definition.val: A quality that inheres in an bearer by virtue of how that bearer interacts with radiation.
A quality of an object that has a value that is increased compared to normal or average.

A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

Q1 has_part Q2 if and only if: every instance of Q1 is a quality_of an entity that has_quality some Q2.

basicPropertyValues.val: We use the has_part relation to relate complex qualities to more primitive ones. A complex quality is a collection of qualities. The complex quality cannot exist without the sub-qualities. For example, the quality 'swollen' necessarily comes with the qualities of 'protruding' and 'increased size'.

definition.val: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being kept below its freezing point.
A branchiness quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's lacking branches.
A single physical entity inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's quantities or relative ratios of subparts.

basicPropertyValues.val: For example calcium composition (which may inhere in bone), haemoglobin composition (which may inhere in blood).

definition.val: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.
A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.
A composition quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's containing granules.

A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

A hardness quality of giving little resistance to pressure.
A hardness quality of being rigid and resistant to pressure.

definition.val: An optical quality which obtains by virtue of the ability of the bearer to absorb visible light.

basicPropertyValues.val: Relational qualities are qualities that hold between multiple entities. Normal (monadic) qualities such as the shape of a eyeball exist purely as a quality of that eyeball. A relational quality such as sensitivity to light is a quality of that eyeball (and connecting nervous system) as it relates to incoming light waves/particles.

definition.val: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having an oblique or slanted direction.
A quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the amount of the bearer's there is mixed with another substance.

An increase in porosity.
An decrease in porosity.

A positional quality inhering in a bearer by virtue the bearer's being changed in position.
